cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about object recognition using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new loss function to address the problem of long-tailed datasets, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of state-of-the-art object detection methods, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL) since object detection is often used in image captioning and other NLP tasks. Finally, the paper mentions the use of gradients in network parameter updating, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
